{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.23",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 23,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 23 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:1",
      "text": "When thou shalt sit to eat with a prince, consider diligently what is set before thy face:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:2",
      "text": "And put a knife to thy throat, if it be so that thou have thy soul in thy own power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:3",
      "text": "Be not desirous of his meats, in which is the bread of deceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:4",
      "text": "Labour not to be rich: but set bounds to thy prudence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:5",
      "text": "Lift not up thy eyes to riches which thou canst not have: because they shall make themselves wings like those of an eagle, and shall fly towards heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:6",
      "text": "Eat not with an envious man, and desire not his meats:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:7",
      "text": "Because, like a soothsayer, and diviner, he thinketh that which he knoweth not. Eat and drink, will he say to thee: and his mind is not with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:8",
      "text": "The meats which thou hadst eaten, thou shalt vomit up: and shalt loose thy beautiful words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:9",
      "text": "Speak not in the ears of fools: because they will despise the instruction of thy speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:10",
      "text": "Touch not the bounds of little ones: and enter not into the field of the fatherless:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:11",
      "text": "For their near kinsman is strong: and he will judge their cause against thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:12",
      "text": "Let thy heart apply itself to instruction and thy ears to words of knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:13",
      "text": "Withhold not correction from a child: for if thou strike him with the rod, he shall not die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:14",
      "text": "Thou shalt beat him with the rod, and deliver his soul from hell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:15",
      "text": "My son, if thy mind be wise, my heart shall rejoice with thee:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:16",
      "text": "And my reins shall rejoice, when thy lips shall speak what is right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:17",
      "text": "Let not thy heart envy sinners: but be thou in the fear of the Lord all the day long:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:18",
      "text": "Because thou shalt have hope in the latter end, and thy expectation shall not be taken away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:19",
      "text": "Hear thou, my son, and be wise: and guide thy mind in the way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:20",
      "text": "Be not in the feasts of great drinkers, nor in their revellings, who contribute flesh to eat:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:21",
      "text": "Because they that give themselves to drinking, and that club together, shall be consumed: and drowsiness shall be clothed with rags.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:22",
      "text": "Hearken to thy father, that begot thee: and despise not thy mother when she is old.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:23",
      "text": "Buy truth, and do not sell wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:24",
      "text": "The father of the just rejoiceth greatly: he that hath begotten a wise son, shall have joy in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:25",
      "text": "Let thy father and thy mother be joyful, and let her rejoice that bore thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:26",
      "text": "My son, give me thy heart: and let thy eyes keep my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:27",
      "text": "For a harlot is a deep ditch: and a strange woman is a narrow pit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:28",
      "text": "She lieth in wait in the way as a robber, and him whom she shall see unwary, she will kill.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:29",
      "text": "Who hath woe? whose father hath woe? who hath contentions? who falls into pits? who hath wounds without cause? who hath redness of eyes?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:30",
      "text": "Surely they that pass their time in wine, and study to drink off their cups.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:31",
      "text": "Look not upon the wine when it is yellow, when the colour thereof shineth in the glass: it goeth in pleasantly,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:32",
      "text": "But in the end, it will bite like a snake, and will spread abroad poison like a basilisk.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:33",
      "text": "Thy eyes shall behold strange women, and thy heart shall utter perverse things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:34",
      "text": "And thou shalt be as one sleeping in the midst of the sea, and as a pilot fast asleep when the stern is lost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.23.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:35",
      "text": "And thou shalt say: They have beaten me, but I was not sensible of pain: they drew me, and I felt not: when shall I awake and find wine again?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
